(* 

base types: int, bool, unit, char
compound types: tuples, lists, options

3 most important type building-blocks (for compound types) in *any* language:
- 'each of': a t value contains values of each of t1, t2... tn
- 'one of: a t value contains values of one of t1, t2... tn
- 'self reference': a t value can refer to other t values (recursion)

Examples so far:

- 'each of': tuples
- 'one of': options
- lists use all three

*)
